<inglise> Acting in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 251 of the Treaty, in the light of the joint text approved by the Conciliation Committee on 9 December 1999(3), </inglise>
<eesti> toimides asutamislepingu artiklis 251 s&auml;testatud korras vastavalt lepituskomisjonis 9. detsembril 1999 heakskiidetud &uuml;histekstile (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Culture has an important intrinsic value to all people in Europe, is an essential element of European integration and contributes to the affirmation and vitality of the European model of society and to the Community's influence on the international scene. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) kultuuril on k&otilde;ikide Euroopa rahvaste jaoks oluline v&auml;&auml;rtus, sel on t&auml;htis osa Euroopa integratsioonis ning see aitab kaasa Euroopa &uuml;hiskonnamudeli kinnistumisele ja eluj&otilde;ulisusele, tugevdades &uuml;htlasi &uuml;henduse m&otilde;ju rahvusvahelisel areenil; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Culture is both an economic factor and a factor in social integration and citizenship; for that reason, it has an important role to play in meeting the new challenges facing the Community, such as globalisation, the information society, social cohesion and the creation of employment. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) kultuur on nii majandust kui ka sotsiaalset integratsiooni ja kodakondsust m&otilde;jutav tegur; seep&auml;rast on kultuuril t&auml;ita t&auml;htis osa &uuml;henduse ees seisvate uute probleemide (globaliseerumine, info&uuml;hiskond, sotsiaalne &uuml;htekuuluvus ja t&ouml;&ouml;kohtade loomine) lahendamises; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) With a view to meeting the needs of the cultural dimension in the European Union, the Community has to take cultural aspects into account in its action under provisions of the Treaty other than Article 151, in particular in order to respect and to promote the diversity of its cultures; in this context, the Commission should encourage the dissemination of information about the opportunities for the cultural industries in the Structural Funds, in accordance with Council Regulation (EC) No 1260/1999 of 21 June 1999 laying down general provisions on the Structural Funds(4), and undertake studies to that end. </inglise>
<eesti> 3) Euroopa Liidu kultuurim&otilde;&otilde;tme vajaduste rahuldamist silmas pidades tuleb &uuml;hendusel asutamislepingu s&auml;tete, v.a artikkel 151, kohaselt toimides v&otilde;tta arvesse eri kultuuriaspekte eesk&auml;tt selleks, et respekteerida ja edendada oma kultuurilist mitmekesisust; seoses sellega peaks &uuml;hendus vastavalt n&otilde;ukogu 21. juuni 1999. aasta m&auml;&auml;rusele (E&Uuml;) nr 1260/1999 (millega kehtestatakse struktuurifondide &uuml;lds&auml;tted) (4) soodustama kultuurit&ouml;&ouml;stuse v&otilde;imalusi struktuurifondides k&auml;sitleva teabe levitamist ja korraldama sel eesm&auml;rgil uuringuid; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) In view of the growing importance of culture for European society and the challenges facing the Community at the dawn of the 21st century, it is important to increase the effectiveness and consistency of Community measures in the cultural field by proposing a single guidance and programming framework for the period 2000 to 2004, bearing in mind the need for the Community policies concerned to take greater account of culture; in this respect, the Council Decision of 22 September 1997 regarding the future of European cultural action(5) calls on the Commission to make proposals with a view to establishing a single instrument for programming and financing aimed at the implementation of Article 151 of the Treaty. </inglise>
<eesti> 4) pidades silmas kultuuri suurenevat t&auml;htust Euroopa &uuml;hiskonnas ning 21. sajandi k&uuml;nnisel &uuml;henduse ees seisvaid probleeme, on vaja muuta &uuml;henduse meetmed kultuurivaldkonnas t&otilde;husamaks ja j&auml;rjepidevamaks, pannes aastateks 2000-2004 ette &uuml;htse arendus- ja planeerimisraamistiku ning pidades silmas vajadust, et &uuml;henduse asjaomane poliitika p&ouml;&ouml;raks kultuurile suuremat t&auml;helepanu; 22. septembri 1997. aasta otsusega, mis k&auml;sitleb Euroopa kultuurimeetmete tulevikku, (5) kutsus n&otilde;ukogu komisjoni &uuml;les tegema ettepanekuid selleks, et asutada &uuml;htne rahastamis- ja planeerimisvahend, mille eesm&auml;rk on asutamislepingu artikli 151 rakendamine; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) If citizens give their full support to, and participate fully in, European integration, greater emphasis should be placed on their common cultural values and roots as a key element of their identity and their membership of a society founded on freedom, democracy, tolerance and solidarity; a better balance should be achieved between the economic and cultural aspects of the Community, so that these aspects can complement and sustain each other. </inglise>
<eesti> 5) et kodanikud toetaksid t&auml;ielikult Euroopa integratsiooni ning osaleksid selles t&auml;iel m&auml;&auml;ral, tuleks panna suuremat r&otilde;hku nende kultuurilistele &uuml;hisv&auml;&auml;rtustele ja juurtele kui nende identiteedi ning vabadusel, demokraatial, sallivusel ja solidaarsusel p&otilde;hinevasse &uuml;hiskonda kuulumise kesksele tegurile; &uuml;henduse majanduslike ja kultuuriliste tahkude vahel tuleks saavutada parem tasakaal, et need tahud saaksid &uuml;ksteist t&auml;iendada ja tugevdada; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) The Treaty confers responsibility on the European Union for creating and ever-closer union among the peoples of Europe and for contributing to the flowering of the cultures of the Member States, while respecting their national and regional diversity and at the same time bringing the common cultural heritage to the fore; special attention should be devoted to safeguarding the position of Europe's small cultures and less widely-spoken languages. </inglise>
<eesti> 6) asutamislepingu kohaselt vastutab Euroopa &Uuml;hendus Euroopa rahvaste &uuml;ha tihedama liidu loomise ja liikmesriikide kultuuri &otilde;itsengu soodustamise eest, &uuml;htlasi respekteerides nende rahvuslikku ja regionaalset mitmekesisust ning samal ajal r&otilde;hutades &uuml;hist kultuurip&auml;randit; erilist t&auml;helepanu tuleks p&ouml;&ouml;rata Euroopa v&auml;ikekultuuride ja v&auml;hem levinud keelte staatuse kaitsmisele; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) The Community is consequently committed to working towards the development of a cultural area common to the European people, which is open, varied and founded on the principle of subsidiarity, cooperation between all those involved in the cultural sector, the promotion of a legislative framework conducive to cultural activities and ensuring respect for cultural diversity, and the integration of the cultural dimension into Community policies as provided for in Article 151(4) of the Treaty. </inglise>
<eesti> 7) j&auml;relikult on &uuml;hendus kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;tama Euroopa rahvaste &uuml;hise kultuuripiirkonna arendamise suunas, mis on avatud, varieeruv ja p&otilde;hineb subsidiaarsuse p&otilde;him&otilde;ttel, kultuuriasutuste koost&ouml;&ouml;l, kultuuritegevust soodustaval ja kultuuri mitmekesisuse respekteerimist tagaval &otilde;igusraamistikul ning asutamislepingu artikli 151 l&otilde;ike 4 kohaselt kultuurim&otilde;&otilde;tme integreerimisel &uuml;henduse poliitikasse, </eesti>
<inglise> (8) To bring to life the cultural area common to the European people, it is essential to encourage creative activities, promote cultural heritage with a European dimension, encourage mutual awareness of the culture and history of the peoples of Europe and support cultural exchanges with a view to improving the dissemination of knowledge and stimulating cooperation and creative activities. </inglise>
<eesti> 8) Euroopa rahvaste &uuml;hise kultuuripiirkonna ellukutsumiseks on oluline ergutada loometegevust, edendada Euroopa m&otilde;&otilde;tmega kultuurip&auml;randit, soodustada Euroopa rahvaste kultuuri ja ajaloo vastastikust tundma&otilde;ppimist ning toetada kultuurivahetust, et parandada teadmiste levitamist ning ergutada koost&ouml;&ouml;d ja loometegevust; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) There is a need, in this context, to promote greater cooperation with those engaged in cultural activities by encouraging them to enter into cooperation agreements for the implementation of joint projects, to support more closely targeted measures having a high European profile, to provide support for specific and innovative measures and to encourage exchanges and dialogue on selected topics of European interest. </inglise>
<eesti> 9) sellega seoses on vaja edendada tihedamat koost&ouml;&ouml;d kultuuri vallas h&otilde;ivatutega, ergutades neid s&otilde;lmima koost&ouml;&ouml;lepinguid &uuml;hisprojektide elluviimiseks, toetada tugevamini eesm&auml;rgistatud meetmeid, millel on selgepiiriline t&auml;hendus Euroopale, eriomaseid ja uuenduslikke meetmeid ning soodustada dialoogi v&auml;ljavalitud, &uuml;leeuroopalist huvi pakkuvatel teemadel; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) The Kaleidoscope, Ariane and Raphael cultural programmes set out, respectively, in Decision No 719/96/EC(6), in Decision No 2085/97/EC(7) and in Decision No 2228/97/EC(8) of the European Parliament and of the Council marked the first positive stage in the implementation of Community action on culture; however, the Community's cultural endeavours should be simplified and reinforced on the basis of the results of the evaluation and achievements of the abovementioned programmes. </inglise>
