<inglise> In the implementation of the Culture 2000 programme, the Commission shall, in cooperation with the Member States, ensure the overall consistency and complementarity with relevant Community policies and actions having an impact on the field of culture. </inglise>
<eesti> Programmi Kultuur 2000 rakendamisel tagab komisjon koost&ouml;&ouml;s liikmesriikidega &uuml;henduse asjakohast kultuurivaldkonda m&otilde;jutava poliitika ja meetmete &uuml;ldise j&auml;rjepidevuse ja vastastikuse t&auml;iendavuse. </eesti>
<inglise> This could involve the possibility of including complementary projects financed through other Community programmes. </inglise>
<eesti> See v&otilde;iks t&auml;hendada v&otilde;imalust kaasata t&auml;iendavaid projekte, mida finantseeritakse &uuml;henduse teiste programmide kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> Third countries and international organisations </inglise>
<eesti> Kolmandad riigid ja rahvusvahelised organisatsioonid </eesti>
<inglise> The Culture 2000 programme shall be open to participation by the countries of the European Economic Area and also to participation by Cyprus and the associated countries of central and eastern Europe in accordance with the conditions laid down in the Association Agreements or in the additional Protocols to the Association Agreements relating to participation in Community programmes concluded or to be concluded with those countries. </inglise>
<eesti> Programm Kultuur 2000 on avatud Euroopa Majanduspiirkonna riikide, samuti K&uuml;prose ning assotsieerunud Kesk- ja Ida-Euroopa riikide osalusele vastavalt tingimustele, mis on s&auml;testatud assotsieerumislepingutes v&otilde;i &uuml;henduse programmides osalemist k&auml;sitlevates assotsieerumislepingute lisaprotokollides, mis on nende riikidega s&otilde;lmitud v&otilde;i tuleb s&otilde;lmida. </eesti>
<inglise> The Culture 2000 programme shall also permit cooperation with other third countries which have concluded Association or Cooperation Agreements containing cultural clauses, on the basis of additional funds made available in accordance with procedures to be agreed with the countries in question. </inglise>
<eesti> Programm Kultuur 2000 v&otilde;imaldab koost&ouml;&ouml;d ka teiste kolmandate riikidega, kes on s&otilde;lminud kultuuriklauslit sisaldava assotsieerumis- v&otilde;i koost&ouml;&ouml;lepingu, kasutades selleks k&otilde;nealuste riikidega kokku lepitava korra kohaselt k&auml;ttesaadavaks tehtavaid lisavahendeid. </eesti>
<inglise> The Culture 2000 programme shall permit joint action with international organisations competent in the field of culture, such as Unesco or the Council of Europe, on the basis of joint contributions and in accordance with the various rules prevailing in each institution or organisation for the realisation of the cultural actions and events listed in Article 2. </inglise>
<eesti> Programm Kultuur 2000 v&otilde;imaldab v&otilde;tta &uuml;hismeetmeid kultuurivaldkonnas p&auml;devate rahvusvaheliste organisatsioonidega, n&auml;iteks UNESCO v&otilde;i Euroopa N&otilde;ukoguga &uuml;hise panuse alusel ja koosk&otilde;las iga institutsiooni v&otilde;i organisatsiooni erinevate eeskirjadega artiklis 2 loetletud kultuurimeetmete ja -&uuml;rituste elluviimise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> Evaluation and monitoring </inglise>
<eesti> Hindamine ja j&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise> Not later than 31 December 2002 the Commission shall present to the European Parliament, the Council, the Economic and Social Committee and the Committee of the Regions a detailed assessment report on the results of the Culture 2000 programme, having regard to its objectives, and accompanied if necessary by a proposal for the amendment of this Decision. </inglise>
<eesti> Hiljemalt 31. detsembriks 2002 esitab komisjon Euroopa Parlamendile, n&otilde;ukogule, majandus- ja sotsiaalkomiteele ning regioonide komiteele programmi Kultuur 2000 tulemuste kohta &uuml;ksikasjaliku hinnanguaruande, v&otilde;ttes arvesse programmi eesm&auml;rke, ja lisab vajaduse korral k&auml;esoleva otsuse muutmise ettepaneku. </eesti>
<inglise> On completion of the Culture 2000 programme, the Commission shall present a report on its implementation to the European Parliament, the Council, the Economic and Social Committee and the Committee of the Regions. </inglise>
<eesti> Programmi Kultuur 2000 l&otilde;petamisel esitab komisjon Euroopa Parlamendile, n&otilde;ukogule ning majandus- ja sotsiaalkomiteele ning regioonide komiteele programmi rakendamisaruande. </eesti>
<inglise> Moreover, the Commission shall present annually a short report monitoring the situation of the implementation of the Culture 2000 programme to the European Parliament, the Council and the Committee of the Regions. </inglise>
<eesti> Peale selle esitab komisjon Euroopa Parlamendile, n&otilde;ukogule ning majandus- ja sotsiaalkomiteele ning regioonide komiteele igal aastal programmi Kultuur 2000 rakendamisolukorra kohta l&uuml;hikese j&auml;relevalvearuande. </eesti>
<inglise> These assessment reports shall emphasise in particular the creation of added value, particularly of a cultural nature, and the socioeconomic consequences of the Community's financial support. </inglise>
